  "body": "UCP #7223 \r\n\r\n### What problem does this PR solve?\r\n\r\nIssue Number: close #7223\r\n\r\nProblem Summary: Currently, if Lightning or BR crashes, the TiKV nodes will be left in the import mode until the user manually switch them back into the normal mode.\r\n\r\n### What is changed and how it works?\r\n\r\nWhat's Changed: In `ImportModeSwitcher`, a background future is added to put TiKV back into normal mode after the timeout.\r\n\r\n### Related changes\r\n\r\n### Check List <!--REMOVE the items that are not applicable-->\r\n\r\nTests <!-- At least one of them must be included. -->\r\n\r\n- Unit test\r\n\r\nSide effects\r\n- A new configuration for import mode timeout is added.\r\n\r\n### Release note <!-- bugfixes or new feature need a release note -->",
